---

Boil a half-full #kettle{} for the couscous.

While it comes to the boil, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and 
seeds. Chop into 1cm chunks. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a 
#garlic press{}). Drain the @sweetcorn{150%g} in a #sieve{}.

Put the @couscous{110%g} in a #medium bowl{}. Pour in the @boiling water{220%ml} 
for the couscous, stir in half the @chicken stock paste{20%g}, then cover tightly 
with #cling film{}. Leave to the side for ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @?oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the pan is hot, add the @British pork mince{120%g}, pepper and sweetcorn. 
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir-fry until the mince has browned and the pepper has softened, ~{6-7%minutes}. 
Use a #spoon{} to break the mince up as it cooks. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and 
equipment after handling raw mince.

Once the pork is cooked, drain and discard any excess fat. IMPORTANT: The pork is 
cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the garlic and cook for another ~{1%minute}. Add the @tomato passata{1},
@chipotle paste{20%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), remaining 
chicken stock paste, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{100%ml} for the sauce and stir 
to combine.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, 
~{4-5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, zest and cut the @lime{1} into wedges. Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(stalks and all). Grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{30%g}.

Once the sauce has thickened, season with salt, pepper and a squeeze of lime 
juice. Remove from the heat.

Fluff the couscous up with a #fork{} then stir in the lime zest and half the 
coriander.

Share the couscous between your bowls.

Spoon over the chipotle pork and finish by sprinkling over the Cheddar and 
remaining coriander.

Serve the remaining lime wedges on the side for squeezing over. Enjoy!